text: Alparslan Baran (born 25 March 2005) is an Austrian football player. He plays as midfielder for FC Liefering in the the Austrian 2. League. ==Career== Baran began his career at ASV Bewegung Steyr. In September 2017 he moved to SK Vorwärts Steyr. For the 2018–19 season he came to the youth team of FC Red Bull Salzburg. He went through all age groups in the Red Bull Salzburg academy from the 2019–20 season. In February 2022 he was in the squad of FC Liefering for the first time. In this season he did not play. He made his debut in the 2nd division in April 2023. He came on in a substitute for Douglas Mendes against Floridsdorfer AC. ==International== Baran played for an Austrian U15 national team for the first time in October 2019. In April 2022 he made his debut against Romania in the U-17 team. He made his U-18 debut against Sweden in September 2022. ==Other websites== Category:2005 births Category:Living people Category:Austrian footballers Category:FC Liefering players Category:Austrian football midfielders
